        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:03PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Carson, or 10 miles south of Colorado Springs, moving northeast
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Colorado Springs, Fountain, Fort Carson, Stratmoor,
Security, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
